以下係用你提供嘅詞語所造嘅句子：

3. 養聲
廣東話：歌手喺開騷前幾日都會特別注意養聲，唔敢食太凍或者太辣嘅嘢。
English: Singers will also pay special attention to vocal care a few days before the concert and dare not eat anything too cold or spicy.

4. 票尾
廣東話：我將張戲票嘅票尾撕落嚟，留做紀念。
English: I tore off the stub of the ticket and kept it as a souvenir.

5. hacker
廣東話：呢個 hacker 入侵咗公司嘅系統，偷走咗好多客戶資料。
English: This hacker hacked into the company's system and stole a lot of customer data.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：屋企陽台種咗幾盆石斛蘭，開花嘅時候好靚。
English: I planted a few pots of Dendrobium on the balcony, and they look beautiful when they bloom.

7. 吊詭 (矛盾、悖論)
廣東話：呢個故事有個好吊詭嘅結局，讀者完全估唔到。
English: This story has a very paradoxical ending that readers could never have guessed.

8. 吊詭 (似非而是、荒謬)
廣東話：世事真係好吊詭，越係想快嘅時候，反而越慢。
English: Life is really absurd; the more you want to be fast, the slower it becomes.

9. 各為其主
廣東話：兩隊球員雖然私底下係好朋友，但係喺場上因為各為其主，所以打得好激烈。
English: Although the players on both teams are good friends off the field, they played very fiercely because each was serving their own master.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：佢嘅車軨蓋撞親咗，需要去車房維修。
English: The rim cover of his car got dented and needs to be repaired at the garage.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：週末我哋會去高爾夫球場打哥夫，放鬆一下心情。
English: On weekends, we go to the golf course to play golf to relax.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間店賣嘅衣服係免揀嘅，買咗就唔可以退。
English: The clothes sold in this shop are non-selectable; once bought, they cannot be returned.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢成日都係擺闊佬，其實口袋入面冇幾多錢。
English: He always acts like a big shot, but actually doesn't have much money in his pocket.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我鍾意聽舊式嘅廣播劇，聲音演繹得好生動。
English: I like listening to old-fashioned radio dramas; the voice acting is very vivid.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：舊時我哋會用錄影機錄低電視節目，留待日後重溫。
English: In the past, we used video recorders to record TV programs to watch later.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：證據擺喺度，佢想抵賴都係吟詩吟唔甩。
English: The evidence is right there; he can't deny it no matter how hard he tries.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：教會每年都會舉行一次大型嘅佈道大會，吸引好多信徒參加。
English: The church holds a large-scale evangelism conference every year, attracting many believers.

18. 寫手 (寫作的人)
廣東話：佢係一名專業嘅寫手，專門替網誌撰寫文章。
English: He is a professional writer who specializes in writing articles for blogs.

19. 寫手 (代替他人寫作的人)
廣東話：因為趕唔切交報告，佢只好搵個寫手幫手代筆。
English: Because he couldn't finish the report in time, he had to hire a ghostwriter to help him write it.

20. 代打
廣東話：佢今日唔得閒，叫咗朋友幫佢代打遊戲。
English: He wasn't free today, so he asked a friend to play the game for him.

21. 茶碗
廣東話：呢套日本茶碗好精緻，適合用來品嚐抹茶。
English: This set of Japanese tea bowls is very exquisite and suitable for drinking matcha.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：斟茶嘅時候記得放個茶隔，以免茶葉飲落去。
English: Remember to put a tea strainer when pouring tea to avoid drinking the tea leaves.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：公司規定員工唔準遲到，但老闆自己遲到卻冇事，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The company rules say employees can't be late, but the boss can be late without any consequences; it's truly "only the magistrate is allowed to set fires, but commoners are not allowed to light lamps."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：演唱會最後一首歌係由主唱獨唱，氣氛好感人。
English: The last song of the concert was sung solo by the lead singer, and the atmosphere was very touching.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢做事快人快事，從來唔會拖泥帶水。
English: He gets things done quickly and decisively, never dragging his feet.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：佢哋喺公廁入面搞出嚟嘅事，真係令人尷尬，俗稱四腳獸。
English: What they did in the public restroom is really embarrassing, commonly referred to as "four-legged beasts."

27. 無米粥
廣東話：我哋今日只係煲無米粥，簡單聊聊合作意向，細節之後再議。
English: We're just having a preliminary talk today, discussing the general intent to cooperate; details will be discussed later.

28. 義會
廣東話：以前街坊之間會組織義會，互相幫助解決經濟困難。
English: In the past, neighbors would organize mutual aid associations to help each other solve financial difficulties.

29. 榜文
廣東話：古代皇帝會貼出榜文，宣佈重要嘅政令。
English: In ancient times, emperors would post proclamations to announce important decrees.

30. MK名
廣東話：佢個 MK名 加咗好多奇怪嘅符號，好難記。
English: His MK name has a lot of strange symbols added to it, making it hard to remember. [end of text]


